"'''The Last Hand'''" is a short story written by [[Paul Danner]] that was originally published in [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 13|''Star Wars Adventure Journal'' 13]] by [[West End Games]] in [[May]] [[1997]], and later republished in ''[[Tales from the New Republic]]'' by [[Bantam Spectra]] in [[December]] [[1999]].

==Plot summary==
During the time of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], [[Gambling/Legends|gambler]] [[Kinnin Vo-Shay]] wins a fortune off the ill-tempered [[Herglic/Legends|Herglic]] [[Doune]], while playing on the behalf of wide-eyed farmboy [[Nyo]]. Nyo aspires to be a [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]], so Vo-Shay agrees to [[Transport/Legends|transport]] him to the [[Black market/Legends|black markets]] of [[Nar Shaddaa/Legends|Nar Shaddaa]] to buy a [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]]. A spiteful Doune buys the lightsaber from the dealer first and offers it up as a prize if Vo-Shay will once again play a single hand of [[Sabacc/Legends|sabacc]] with him. Vo-Shay loses and is forced to hand over a [[Necklace/Legends|necklace]] believed to be the source of his incredible luck. Vo-Shay admits to Nyo that the necklace is merely a bauble; he lost the game on purpose to douse Doune's fiery vengeance. Feeling gleeful over his triumph, Doune gives the lightsaber to Nyo anyway.

